Title: Whiplash
Plot: 뛰어난 잠재력을 가진 유망한 젊은 드러머가 꿈을 펼치기 위해 셰이퍼 음악학교에 입학한다. 최고의 지휘자이자 최고의 폭군인 플래처 교수는 폭언과 학대로 그를 한계까지 몰아붙인다.

Title: Birdman: Or (The Unexpected Virtue of Ignorance)
Plot: A washed-up actor, who once played an iconic superhero, battles his ego and attempts to recover his family, his career and himself in the days leading up to the opening of his Broadway play.

Title: American Sniper
Plot: 네이비 씰의 저격수 크리스 카일은 전장에서 수 많은 생명을 구하고 전설로 남게 된다. 4번의 아프가니스탄 파병을 마치고 아내와 아이가 있는 집으로 돌아온 크리스는 전쟁이 남긴 상처를 깨닿게 된다.

Title: Boyhood
Plot: 메이슨의 삶, 어린 시절에서 대학에 입학할 때 까지의 이야기. 여섯살의 메이슨은 누나 사만다와 어머니 올리비아와 함께 살고 있다. 아빠는 일주일에 한번씩 들러 아이들과 친구처럼 놀아주지만 함께 살 수는 없다. 엄마의 이혼과 재혼, 직장 문제 등으로 계속 낮선 도시로 이사를 다녀야 하는 메이슨은 외로운 나날을 보내며 성장한다.

Title: The Imitation Game
Plot: 2차 대전 당시, 수학자 앨런 튜링은 이니그마 암호를 훌기위해 동료 수학자들과 협력하여 프로젝트를 수행한다.

Title: The Grand Budapest Hotel
Plot: 1927년 1차 세계대전 중, 세계 최고의 부호 마담 D.가 의문의 살인을 당하고, 그녀의 연인이자 전설적인 호텔 컨시어지인 구스타브가 용의자로 몰린다. 구스파브는 누명을 벗기 위해 신뢰하는 친구이자 호텔 로비보이인 제로에게 도움을 청한다.

Title: Selma
Plot: A chronicle of Martin Luther King‘s campaign to secure equal voting rights via an epic march from Selma to Montgomery, Alabama in 1965.

Title: The Theory of Everything
Plot: A look at the relationship between the famous physicist Stephen Hawking and his wife.

Title: Foxcatcher
Plot: The greatest Olympic Wrestling Champion brother team joins Team Foxcatcher led by multimillionaire sponsor John E. du Pont as they train for the 1988 games in Seoul - a union that leads to unlikely circumstances.

Title: Still Alice
Plot: 언어학 교수로서 존경받는 삶을 살던 앨리스는 어느날 자신이 희귀한 알츠하이머에 걸렸다는 것을 알게된다. 자신의 모든 기억, 심지어 사랑하는 사람들까지도 모두 잊어버릴 수 있다는 두려움에 떨게되고 이는 가족 모두에게도 두려움으로 다가온다.

Title: Two Days, One Night
Plot: 벨기에의 젊은 어머니 산드라는 직장 동료들이 해고에 대한 대가로 상당한 급여 보너스를 선택했다는 사실을 알게된다. 그녀는 1주일 동안 보너스를 대신 직장을 유지하도록 설득하려 한다.

Title: Gone Girl
Plot: With his wife‘s disappearance having become the focus of an intense media circus, a man sees the spotlight turned on him when it‘s suspected that he may not be innocent.

Title: Wild
Plot: 한 여성이 그녀의 무절제한 생활과 슬픔에서 벗어나기 위해 1,100 마일을 혼자 걷는 멀고 힘든 여정을 떠난다.

Title: The Judge
Plot: 변호사 행크 팔머는 어머니의 부고 소식을 듣고 어린 시절의 집으로 돌아가는데, 마을의 판사인 아버지가 살인 혐의를 받는다. 행크는 진실을 찾기 위해 위해 노력하고 그 과정에서 소원했던 가족의 소중함을 깨닫는다.

Title: Into the Woods
Plot: 마녀는 자녀가 없는 빵 굽는 사람과 그의 아내에게 고전 동화에서 마법 아이템을 구해 가문에 가해진 저주를 건다.

Title: Nightcrawler
Plot: When Lou Bloom, a driven man desperate for work, muscles into the world of L.A. crime journalism, he blurs the line between observer and participant to become the star of his own story. Aiding him in his effort is Nina, a TV-news veteran.

Title: Inherent Vice
Plot: In 1970, drug-fueled Los Angeles detective Larry Doc" Sportello investigates the disappearance of a former girlfriend."

Title: Mr. Turner
Plot: An exploration of the last quarter century of the great, if eccentric, British painter J.M.W. Turner‘s life.

Title: Unbroken
Plot: After a near-fatal plane crash in WWII, Olympian Louis Zamperini spends a harrowing 47 days in a raft with two fellow crewmen before he‘s caught by the Japanese navy and sent to a prisoner-of-war camp.

Title: Ida
Plot: 1960년대, 폴란드의 수녀원에서 가족의 존재조차 모르고 자란 소녀 안나는 이모의 존재를 알게되고, 독일 점령당시의 가족의 비밀을 알게된다.

Title: Maleficent
Plot: A vengeful fairy is driven to curse an infant princess, only to discover that the child may be the one person who can restore peace to their troubled land.

Title: Interstellar
Plot: 환경 오염으로 지구가 더이상 인간이 살 수 없는 것이 되고, 인류는 웜홀을 통해 인류가 생존할 수 있는 방법을 찾으려 한다.

Title: The Hobbit: The Battle of the Five Armies
Plot: Bilbo and Company are forced to engage in a war against an array of combatants and keep the Lonely Mountain from falling into the hands of a rising darkness.

Title: Captain America: The Winter Soldier
Plot: 캡틴 아메리카는 현대 사회에서 자신의 역할을 받아들이기 위해 쉴드에서 여러 작전에 투입되어 노력하지만, 쉴드가 하이드라에 장악된 것을 곧 알게된다. 그는 블랙 위도우의 팀을 이루어 새로운 위협인 윈터 솔저와 맞선다.

Title: Dawn of the Planet of the Apes
Plot: 지명적인 질병 판데믹이 일어난 10년 후, 생존한 유인원의 무리가 인간 생존자 그룹과 전투를 벌인다.

Title: Guardians of the Galaxy
Plot: A group of intergalactic criminals are forced to work together to stop a fanatical warrior from taking control of the universe.

Title: X-Men: Days of Future Past
Plot: The X-Men send Wolverine to the past in a desperate effort to change history and prevent an event that results in doom for both humans and mutants.

Title: Begin Again
Plot: 딸이 보는 앞에서 망신을 당한 맨하탄의 음악 프로듀서와 실연의 아픔을 겪는 젊은 여성 싱어 송라이터가 만나 뉴욕에서 새로운 음악을 만들기 시작한다.

Title: The Lego Movie
Plot: An ordinary Lego construction worker, thought to be the prophesied 'Special', is recruited to join a quest to stop an evil tyrant from gluing the Lego universe into eternal stasis.

Title: Beyond the Lights
Plot: The pressures of fame have superstar singer Noni on the edge, until she meets Kaz, a young cop who works to help her find the courage to develop her own voice and break free to become the artist she was meant to be.

Title: Glen Campbell: I‘ll Be Me
Plot: As he struggles with Alzheimer‘s disease, country-music legend Glen Campbell embarks on his farewell tour in the U.S., Australia, and Europe.

Title: Feast
Plot: The story of one man‘s love life is seen through the eyes of his best friend and dog, Winston, and revealed bite by bite through the meals they share.

Title: The Bigger Picture
Plot: ‘You want to put her in a home; you tell her; tell her now!‘ hisses one brother to the other. But Mother won‘t go, and their own lives quickly unravel as she clings to life. Director Daisy Jacobs uses two-metre-high painted characters in full-size sets to tell the stark and darkly humorous tale of caring for an elderly relative. The Bigger Picture is quite simply the most innovative animated short you will see this year.

Title: The Dam Keeper
Plot: A young pig with an important job, and a new friend who changes everything. In a desolate future, one small town has survived because of a large windmill dam that acts as a fan to keep out pollution. The dam‘s operator, Pig, works tirelessly to keep the sails spinning and protect the town, despite abuse from classmates and an indifferent public. When a new student joins Pig‘s class, nothing will be the same again.

Title: Me and My Moulton
Plot: A personal animated story about a girl which wishes for a bicycle from her parents, but gets something completely different, showing the different reality in which children and grown ups live in.

Title: A Single Life
Plot: When Pia plays a mysterious vinyl record single, she suddenly knows how to travel through her own life.

Title: The Phone Call
Plot: Heather is a shy lady who works in a helpline call centre. When she receives a phone call from a mystery man, she has no idea that the encounter will change her life forever.

Title: Aya
Plot: Two strangers unexpectedly meet at an airport. He mistakenly confuses her to be his assigned driver. She, enchanted by the random encounter, does not hurry to prove him wrong.

Title: Boogaloo and Graham
Plot: Jamesy and Malachy are over the moon when their soft-hearted Dad presents them with two baby chicks to care for, but the two boys are in for a shock when their parents announce that big changes are coming to the family.

Title: Butter Lamp
Plot: A young itinerant photographer and his assistant suggest to Tibetan nomads to photograph them in front of various background.

Title: Parvaneh
Plot: Parvaneh is a young Afghan immigrant who recently arrived at a transit centre for asylum seekers in the Swiss Alps. The only things she has got to know yet are the rural area surrounding the centre and the centre itself.

Title: Crisis Hotline: Veterans Press 1
Plot: They served their country overseas. Now, many military veterans must turn to the unique services of the Veterans‘ Crisis Line to help with their own personal and professional traumas at home. This documentary profiles several of the VCL counselors who work the phones of this 24-hour service, providing support, guidance, and hope to active and retired servicemen dealing with emotional, physical and financial troubles.

Title: Joanna
Plot: A story of thoughtfulness in death, life and love.

Title: Our Curse
Plot: The film is a personal statement of the director and his wife, who have to deal with an incurable disease of their newborn son.

Title: The Reaper
Plot: Efrain, also known as the Reaper, who works at a slaughterhouse since 25 years ago, we will discover his deep relationship with dead.

Title: White Earth
Plot: Thousands of desperate souls flock to America‘s Northern Plains seeking work in the oil fields. Three children and an immigrant mother brave a cruel winter and explore themes of innocence, home and the American Dream.

Title: Citizenfour
Plot: A documentarian and a reporter travel to Hong Kong for the first of many meetings with Edward Snowden.

Title: Finding Vivian Maier
Plot: A documentary on the late Vivian Maier, a nanny whose previously unknown cache of 100,000 photographs earned her a posthumous reputation as one of the most accomplished street photographers.

Title: Last Days in Vietnam
Plot: During the chaotic final weeks of the Vietnam War, the North Vietnamese Army closes in on Saigon as the panicked South Vietnamese people desperately attempt to escape. On the ground, American soldiers and diplomats confront the same moral quandary: whether to obey White House orders to evacuate U.S. citizens only--or to risk treason and save the lives of as many South Vietnamese citizens as they can.

Title: Virunga
Plot: A group of brave individuals risk their lives to save the last of the world‘s mountain gorillas; in the midst of renewed civil war and a scramble for Congo‘s natural resources.

Title: Tangerines
Plot: War in Georgia, Apkhazeti region in 1990. An Estonian man Ivo has stayed behind to harvest his crops of tangerines. In a bloody conflict at his door, a wounded man is left behind, and Ivo is forced to take him in.

Title: Leviathan
Plot: In a Russian coastal town, Kolya is forced to fight the corrupt mayor when he is told that his house will be demolished. He recruits a lawyer friend to help, but the man‘s arrival brings further misfortune for Kolya and his family.

Title: Wild Tales
KoreanTitle: 와일드 테일즈: 참을 수 없는 순간
Plot: Six short stories involving distressed people.

Title: Timbuktu
Plot: A cattle herder and his family who reside in the dunes of Timbuktu find their quiet lives -- which are typically free of the Jihadists determined to control their faith -- abruptly disturbed.

Title: Big Hero 6
Plot: The special bond that develops between plus-sized inflatable robot Baymax, and prodigy Hiro Hamada, who team up with a group of friends to form a band of high-tech heroes.

Title: The Boxtrolls
Plot: A young orphaned boy raised by underground cave-dwelling trash collectors tries to save his friends from an evil exterminator. Based on the children‘s novel ‘Here Be Monsters‘ by Alan Snow.

Title: How to Train Your Dragon 2
Plot: 히컵과 투슬리스가 새로운 야생 용과 신비한 드래곤 라이더가 있는 얼음 동굴을 발견하하고, 이 두 친구는 평화를 지키기 위해 전투에 나선다.

Title: Song of the Sea
Plot: Saoirse, a little girl who can turn into a seal, goes on an adventure with her brother to save the spirit world and other magical beings like her.

Title: The Tale of The Princess Kaguya
Plot: Found inside a shining stalk of bamboo by an old bamboo cutter and his wife, a tiny girl grows rapidly into an exquisite young lady. The mysterious young princess enthralls all who encounter her - but ultimately she must confront her fate, the punishment for her crime.

Title: 12 Years a Slave
Plot: 18세기, 뉴욕에서 자유인으로 살던 흑인 솔로몬 노섭은 노예 사냥꾼에게 납치되어 미국 남부로 끌려가 노예로 팔리게 된다.

Title: The Wolf of Wall Street
Plot: Based on the true story of Jordan Belfort, from his rise to a wealthy stock-broker living the high life to his fall involving crime, corruption and the federal government.

Title: American Hustle
Plot: A con man, Irving Rosenfeld, along with his seductive partner Sydney Prosser, is forced to work for a wild FBI agent, Richie DiMaso, who pushes them into a world of Jersey powerbrokers and mafia.

Title: Nebraska
Plot: An aging, booze-addled father makes the trip from Montana to Nebraska with his estranged son in order to claim a million-dollar Mega Sweepstakes Marketing prize.

Title: Captain Phillips
Plot: The true story of Captain Richard Phillips and the 2009 hijacking by Somali pirates of the US-flagged MV Maersk Alabama, the first American cargo ship to be hijacked in two hundred years.

Title: Philomena
Plot: A world-weary political journalist picks up the story of a woman‘s search for her son, who was taken away from her decades ago after she became pregnant and was forced to live in a convent.

Title: Dallas Buyers Club
Plot: In 1985 Dallas, electrician and hustler Ron Woodroof works around the system to help AIDS patients get the medication they need after he is himself diagnosed with the disease.

Title: Gravity
Plot: 허블 우주망원경을 수리하기 위해 우주를 탐사하던 라이언 스톤 박사는 폭파된 인공위성의 잔해와 부딪히면서 소리도 산소도 없는 우주 한 가운데에 홀로 남겨지게 된다.

Title: Her
Plot: A lonely writer develops an unlikely relationship with his newly purchased operating system that‘s designed to meet his every need.

Title: The Salt of the Earth
Plot: For the last 40 years, the photographer Sebastiao Salgado has been travelling through the continents, in the footsteps of an ever-changing humanity. He has witnessed some of the major events of our recent history; international conflicts, starvation and exodus. He is now embarking on the discovery of pristine territories, of wild fauna and flora, and of grandiose landscapes as part of a huge photographic project which is a tribute to the planet‘s beauty.

Title: Blue Jasmine
Plot: A New York socialite, deeply troubled and in denial, arrives in San Francisco to impose upon her sister. She looks a million, but isn‘t bringing money, peace, or love...

Title: August: Osage County
Plot: 독설가 엄마, 이혼 위기에 놓인 큰 딸, 사촌 오빠와 사랑에 빠진 둘째 딸, 언니의 딸에게 치근덕거리는 중년의 약혼자를 가진 셋째 딸, 그리고 이들 못지 않게 문제가 많은 엄마의 여동생 가족들. 8월의 어느 날, 아버지의 장례식에서 가족의 과거가 폭로된다.

Title: Before Midnight
Plot: We meet Jesse and Celine nine years on in Greece. Almost two decades have passed since their first meeting on that train bound for Vienna.

Title: The Grandmaster
Plot: The story of martial-arts master Ip Man, the man who trained Bruce Lee.

Title: Inside Llewyn Davis
Plot: A week in the life of a young singer as he navigates the Greenwich Village folk scene of 1961.

Title: Prisoners
Plot: When Keller Dover‘s daughter and her friend go missing, he takes matters into his own hands as the police pursue multiple leads and the pressure mounts. But just how far will this desperate father go to protect his family?

Title: The Great Gatsby
Plot: A Midwestern war veteran finds himself drawn to the past and lifestyle of his millionaire neighbor.

Title: The Invisible Woman
Plot: At the height of his career, Charles Dickens meets a younger woman who becomes his secret lover until his death.

Title: The Hobbit: The Desolation of Smaug
Plot: 12명의 난쟁이가 빌보, 간달프와 함께 그들의 고향을 사악한 용 스마우그로 부터 되찾기 위해 에레보드레 도착하고, 빌보는 난쟁이들의 보물 아르켄스톤을 찾기 위한 모험을 시작한다.

Title: Lone Survivor
Plot: Marcus Luttrell and his team set out on a mission to capture or kill notorious Taliban leader Ahmad Shah, in late June 2005. Marcus and his team are left to fight for their lives in one of the most valiant efforts of modern warfare.

Title: All Is Lost
Plot: After a collision with a shipping container at sea, a resourceful sailor finds himself, despite all efforts to the contrary, staring his mortality in the face.

Title: Iron Man 3
Plot: 토니 스타크가 과거에 저질렀던 과오로 인해 강력한 테러리스트 집단의 공격을 받게 된다.

Title: Star Trek Into Darkness
Plot: 엔터프라이즈 호의 선원들이 조직 내에서 막기 힘든 테러 세력의 존재를 발견하고, 커크 선장은 이들의 대량 살상 무기를 탈취하기 위해 전쟁 지역으로 들어간다.

Title: Jackass Presents: Bad Grandpa
Plot: 86-year-old Irving Zisman takes a trip from Nebraska to North Carolina to take his 8 year-old grandson, Billy, back to his real father.

Title: Frozen
Plot: 엘사 여왕의 신비로운 힘 때문에 아렌델 왕국이 꽁꽁 얼어붙자, 동생 안나는 엘사를 찾고 저주를 풀기위해 떠난다.

Title: Alone Yet Not Alone
Plot: The year is 1755, and the English colonies are being ravaged by the atrocities of war. Opposing European powers have clashed over the fertile Ohio valley, and entire families are devastated

Title: Despicable Me 2
Plot: When Gru, the world‘s most super-bad turned super-dad has been recruited by a team of officials to stop lethal muscle and a host of Gru‘s own, He has to fight back with new gadgetry, cars, and more minion madness.

Title: Mandela: Long Walk to Freedom
Plot: A chronicle of Nelson Mandela‘s life journey from his childhood in a rural village through to his inauguration as the first democratically elected president of South Africa.

Title: The Book Thief
Plot: While subjected to the horrors of World War II Germany, young Liesel finds solace by stealing books and sharing them with others. In the basement of her home, a Jewish refugee is being sheltered by her adoptive parents.

Title: Saving Mr. Banks
Plot: Author P.L. Travers reflects on her childhood after reluctantly meeting with Walt Disney, who seeks to adapt her Mary Poppins books for the big screen.

Title: Argo
Plot: Acting under the cover of a Hollywood producer scouting a location for a science fiction film, a CIA agent launches a dangerous operation to rescue six Americans in Tehran during the U.S. hostage crisis in Iran in 1980.

Title: Amour
Plot: Georges and Anne are an octogenarian couple. They are cultivated, retired music teachers. Their daughter, also a musician, lives in Britain with her family. One day, Anne has a stroke, and the couple‘s bond of love is severely tested.

Title: Beasts of the Southern Wild
Plot: Faced with both her hot-tempered father‘s fading health and melting ice-caps that flood her ramshackle bayou community and unleash ancient aurochs, six-year-old Hushpuppy must learn the ways of courage and love.

Title: Django Unchained
Plot: 독일인 현상금 사냥꾼에게 구출되어 자유의 몸이 된 흑인 노예 장고는 잔인한 농장주로 부터 아내를 구하기 위해 떠난다

Title: Les Miserables
Plot: 19세기 프랑스, 가석방 조건을 위반하여 수십년 동안 무자비한 경찰관 자베르에게 쫒겨온 장발쟝은 공장 노동자 팡틴의 딸을 돌보기로 결심하고, 이 결정은 그들의 삶은 영원히 바꿔놓는다.

Title: Life of Pi
Plot: 파이라는 이름의 소년이 바다에서 조난을 당해 가족을 잃고 표류하게 된다. 파이는 조난 과정에서 예기치 않게 뱅갈 호랑이 한마리와 좁은 구명 보트에서 함께 표류하게 된다.

Title: Lincoln
Plot: As the Civil War continues to rage, America‘s president struggles with continuing carnage on the battlefield as he fights with many inside his own cabinet on the decision to emancipate the slaves.

Title: Silver Linings Playbook
Plot: After a stint in a mental institution, former teacher Pat Solitano moves back in with his parents and tries to reconcile with his ex-wife. Things get more challenging when Pat meets Tiffany, a mysterious girl with problems of her own.

Title: Zero Dark Thirty
Plot: 2001년 9월의 공격 이후 테러를 감행한 알카에다의 리더 오사바 빈 라덴을 10년간 추적하여 2011년 네이비 씰 6팀이 사실하기 까지의 10년간의 기록.

Title: The Master
Plot: A Naval veteran arrives home from war unsettled and uncertain of his future - until he is tantalized by The Cause and its charismatic leader.

Title: Flight
Plot: An airline pilot saves almost all his passengers on his malfunctioning airliner which eventually crashed, but an investigation into the accident reveals something troubling.

Title: The Impossible
Plot: The story of a tourist family in Thailand caught in the destruction and chaotic aftermath of the 2004 Indian Ocean tsunami.

Title: The Sessions
Plot: A man in an iron lung who wishes to lose his virginity contacts a professional sex surrogate with the help of his therapist and priest.

Title: Moonrise Kingdom
Plot: A pair of young lovers flee their New England town, which causes a local search party to fan out to find them.

Title: Anna Karenina
Plot: In late-19th-century Russian high society, St. Petersburg aristocrat Anna Karenina enters into a life-changing affair with the dashing Count Alexei Vronsky.

Title: Skyfall

Plot: 은퇴를 앞둔 한 프로 레슬러가 링 밖에서의 새로운 삶을 찾고자 싸운다.

Title: Changeling
Plot: 1928년, 싱글맘 크리스틴은 9살 아이가 실종된 것을 알게되고 LA 경찰에 신고한다. 5개월 뒤, 경찰에게 아이를 찾았다고 연락받지만 그 아이는 크리스틴의 아이가 아니었다. 하지만 경찰은 그대로 사건을 종결하려 한다.

Title: Doubt
Plot: A Catholic school principal questions a priest‘s ambiguous relationship with a troubled young student.

Title: Frozen River
Plot: Takes place in the days before Christmas near a little-known border crossing on the Mohawk reservation between New York State and Quebec. Here, the lure of fast money from smuggling presents a daily challenge to single moms who would otherwise be earning minimum wage. Two women - one white, one Mohawk, both single mothers faced with desperate circumstances - are drawn into the world of border smuggling across the frozen water of the St. Lawrence River. Ray and Lila - and a New York State Trooper as opponent in an evolving cat-and-mouse game.

Title: Rachel Getting Married
Plot: A young woman who has been in and out from rehab for the past 10 years returns home for the weekend for her sister‘s wedding

Title: The Dark Knight
Plot: When the menace known as the Joker wreaks havoc and chaos on the people of Gotham, the caped crusader must come to terms with one of the greatest psychological tests of his ability to fight injustice.

Title: Revolutionary Road
Plot: A young couple living in a Connecticut suburb during the mid-1950s struggle to come to terms with their personal problems while trying to raise their two children.

Title: Tropic Thunder
Plot: Through a series of freak occurrences, a group of actors shooting a big-budget war movie are forced to become the soldiers they are portraying.

Title: Vicky Cristina Barcelona
Plot: 가장 친한 친구이지만, 사랑에 관해서는 완전히 상반된 생각을 가지고 있는 비키(레베카 홀)와 크리스티나(스칼렛 요한슨). 바르셀로나에서 휴가를 즐기던 두 사람은 우연히 매력적인 화가 후안 안토니오(하비에르 바르뎀)를 만나게 되고, 그의 노골적인 유혹에 강하게 거부하는 비키롸 달리 크리스티나는 후안에게 묘한 매력을 느낀다. 하지만 예기치 않은 순간에 비키 마저 후안에게 빠져들게 되지만 예정된 결혼을 위해 바르셀로나를 떠난다. 그리고 바르셀로나에 남게 된 크리스티나와 후안이 둘 만의 사랑을 나누던 어느 날, 후안의 전처 마리아(페넬로페 크루즈)가 둘 사이에 나타난다.

Title: Happy-Go-Lucky
Plot: A look at a few chapters in the life of Poppy, a cheery, colorful, North London schoolteacher whose optimism tends to exasperate those around her.

Title: In Bruges
Plot: Guilt-stricken after a job gone wrong, hitman Ray and his partner await orders from their ruthless boss in Bruges, Belgium, the last place in the world Ray wants to be.

Title: WALL·E
Plot: In the distant future, a small waste collecting robot inadvertently embarks on a space journey that will ultimately decide the fate of mankind.

Title: The Duchess
Plot: A chronicle of the life of 18th century aristocrat Georgiana, Duchess of Devonshire, who was reviled for her extravagant political and personal life.

Title: Australia
Plot: Set in northern Australia before World War II, an English aristocrat who inherits a sprawling ranch reluctantly pacts with a stock-man in order to protect her new property from a takeover plot. As the pair drive 2,000 head of cattle over unforgiving landscape, they experience the bombing of Darwin, Australia, by Japanese forces firsthand.

Title: Wanted
Plot: A frustrated office worker learns that he is the son of a professional assassin, and that he shares his father‘s superhuman killing abilities.

Title: Iron Man
Plot: 아프가니스탄의 동굴에 납치되었다가 탈출한 군수 업체 스타크 인더스트리의 회장 토니 스타크는 악과 맞서 싸우기 위한 특별한 수트 형태의 무기를 제작한다. 이는 그의 회사의 정책과 정면으로 대치된다.

Title: Hellboy II: The Golden Army
Plot: The mythical world starts a rebellion against humanity in order to rule the Earth, so Hellboy and his team must save the world from the rebellious creatures.

Title: Defiance
Plot: Jewish brothers in Nazi-occupied Eastern Europe escape into the Belarussian forests, where they join Russian resistance fighters and endeavor to build a village in order to protect themselves and about 1,000 Jewish non-combatants.

Title: No Country for Old Men
Plot: 리오 그랑데 근처에 살던 한 사냥꾼이 우연히 잘못된 경로로 입수한 마약에 의해 폭력과 대혼란이 발생한다.

Title: Atonement
Plot: 13살 신출내기 작가 브리오니 텔리스는 그녀의 언니의 연인이 저지르지 않은 범죄로 인해 여러개의 사람으로의 변화를 경헙한다. 이언 맥이완의 영국 로맨스 소설 원작.

Title: Juno
Plot: 계획되지 않은 임신을 하게 된 어린 소녀가 그녀의 태어나지 않은 아이에 대해 입양 계획을 세우게 된다.

Title: Michael Clayton
Plot: A law firm brings in its fixer" to remedy the situation after a lawyer has a breakdown while representing a chemical company that he knows is guilty in a multi-billion dollar class action suit."

Title: There Will Be Blood
Plot: A story of family, religion, hatred, oil and madness, focusing on a turn-of-the-century prospector in the early days of the business.

Title: Eastern Promises
Plot: A Russian teenager living in London who dies during childbirth leaves clues to a midwife in her journal that could tie her child to a rape involving a violent Russian mob family.

Title: In the Valley of Elah
Plot: 은 한 군사 수사관이 이라크 순방을 마치고 돌아온 아들의 실종에 대한 진실을 밝히기 위해 경찰 수사관과 협력한다.

Title: Sweeney Todd: The Demon Barber of Fleet Street
KoreanTitle: 스위니 토드: 어느 잔혹한 이발사 이야기
Plot: The infamous story of Benjamin Barker, AKA Sweeney Todd, who sets up a barber shop down in London which is the basis for a sinister partnership with his fellow tenant, Mrs. Lovett. Based on the hit Broadway musical.

Title: La Vie en Rose
Plot: 가수 에디트 피아프의 삶 이야기

Title: Away from Her
Plot: A man coping with the institutionalization of his wife because of Alzheimer‘s disease faces an epiphany when she transfers her affections to another man, Aubrey, a wheelchair-bound mute who also is a patient at the nursing home.

Title: Elizabeth: The Golden Age
Plot: A mature Queen Elizabeth endures multiple crises late in her reign including court intrigues, an assassination plot, the Spanish Armada, and romantic disappointments.

Title: The Savages
Plot: A sister and brother face the realities of familial responsibility as they begin to care for their ailing father.

Title: The Assassination of Jesse James by the Coward Robert Ford
KoreanTitle: 비겁한 로버트 포드의 제시 제임스 암살
Plot: 전설적인 갱단 두목 제시 제임스를 어린 시절부터  우상화하면서 자란 로버트 포드는 미주리의 갱단에 합류하고, 동경과 우정으로 시작된 감정은 경쟁이 되고 명성을 향한 욕망은 집착이 된다.

Title: Charlie Wilson‘s War
Plot: A drama based on a Texas congressman Charlie Wilson‘s covert dealings in Afghanistan, where his efforts to assist rebels in their war with the Soviets have some unforeseen and long-reaching effects.

Title: Into the Wild
Plot: After graduating from Emory University, top student and athlete Christopher McCandless abandons his possessions, gives his entire $24,000 savings account to charity and hitchhikes to Alaska to live in the wilderness. Along the way, Christopher encounters a series of characters that shape his life.

Title: American Gangster
Plot: In 1970s America, a detective works to bring down the drug empire of Frank Lucas, a heroin kingpin from Manhattan, who is smuggling the drug into the country from the Far East.

Title: Gone Baby Gone
Plot: Two Boston area detectives investigate a little girl‘s kidnapping, which ultimately turns into a crisis both professionally and personally.

Title: I‘m Not There.
Plot: Ruminations on the life of Bob Dylan, where six characters embody a different aspect of the musician‘s life and work.

Title: The Diving Bell and the Butterfly
Plot: 뇌졸중을 앓고 왼쪽 눈을 제외한 완전히 마비 된 몸으로 살아야하는 Elle 편집장 쟝 도미니크 보비의 실화.

Title: Lars and the Real Girl
Plot: A delusional young man strikes up an unconventional relationship with a doll he finds on the Internet.

Title: Ratatouille
Plot: A rat who can cook makes an unusual alliance with a young kitchen worker at a famous restaurant.

Title: The Golden Compass
Plot: In a parallel universe, young Lyra Belacqua journeys to the far North to save her best friend and other kidnapped children from terrible experiments by a mysterious organization.

Title: Across the Universe
Plot: The music of the Beatles and the Vietnam War form the backdrop for the romance between an upper-class American girl and a poor Liverpudlian artist.

Title: The Bourne Ultimatum
Plot: Jason Bourne dodges a ruthless CIA official and his agents from a new assassination program while searching for the origins of his life as a trained killer.

Title: 3:10 to Yuma
Plot: A small-time rancher agrees to hold a captured outlaw who‘s awaiting a train to go to court in Yuma. A battle of wills ensues as the outlaw tries to psych out the rancher.

Title: Transformers
Plot: 오토봇과 사악한 디셉티콘, 두 사이버트로니안 종족 간에 전쟁이 벌어지고, 고대의 힘이 담긴 올스파크를 찾기 위해 지구를 찾는다.

Title: Pirates of the Caribbean: At World‘s End
Plot: Captain Barbossa, Will Turner and Elizabeth Swann must sail off the edge of the map, navigate treachery and betrayal, and make their final alliances for one last decisive battle.

Title: Norbit
Plot: A mild-mannered guy, who is engaged to a monstrous woman, meets the woman of his dreams, and schemes to find a way to be with her.

Title: Once
Plot: A modern-day musical about a busker and an immigrant and their eventful week in Dublin, as they write, rehearse and record songs that tell their love story.

Title: August Rush
Plot: A drama with fairy tale elements, where an orphaned musical prodigy uses his gift as a clue to finding his birth parents.

Title: Enchanted
Plot: A princess, who is prepared to be wed, is sent away to New York by an evil queen, where she falls in love with a lawyer.

Title: The Kite Runner
Plot: After spending years in California, Amir returns to his homeland in Afghanistan to help his old friend Hassan, whose son is in trouble.

Title: Peter & the Wolf
Plot: An animated retelling set to Prokofiev‘s suite. Peter is a slight lad, solitary, locked out of the woods by his protective grandfather, his only friend a duck. In town, he‘s bullied. When a wolf menaces the duck - as well as grandfather‘s fat cat and an ill-flying bird that Peter has befriended - Peter bravely tries to tree the wolf. Grandfather, the townspeople, and the hunters who have antagonized Peter figure in the denouement.

Title: I Met the Walrus
Plot: The animated illustration of a 14-year-old‘s interview with John Lennon in 1969.

Title: Madame Tutli-Putli
Plot: Madame Tutli-Putli boards the Night Train, weighed down with all her earthly possessions and the ghosts of her past. She travels alone, facing both the kindness and menace of strangers. As day descends into dark, she finds herself caught up in a desperate metaphysical adventure. Adrift between real and imagined worlds, Madame Tutli-Putli confronts her demons and is drawn into an undertow of mystery and suspense. The National Film Board of Canada presents a stunning, stop-motion animated film that takes the viewer on an exhilarating existential journey. The film introduces groundbreaking visual techniques and is supported by a haunting and original score. Painstaking care and craftsmanship in form and detail bring to life a fully imagined, tactile world unlike any you have seen. Jungian thriller? Hitchcockian suspense? Artistic tour de force? The Night Train awaits you.

Title: My Love
Plot: In nineteenth-century Russia, a teenage boy in search of love is drawn to two very different women.

Title: Even Pigeons Go to Heaven
Plot: On a moonlit fall night, a priest races to the home of Mr. Moulin running a motorcycle off the road and arriving just in time to catch the old man as he falls from a chair on which he stacked books in order to reach a bottle of cognac. Mr. Moulin is a miser with a sock full of money that the priest would like to appropriate by selling the old man a space capsule that will take him to paradise. After a test drive and some negotiation, the deal may be struck, but then, there‘s a knock at the door.

Title: Le Mozart des pickpockets
Plot: Richard and Philippe live hand to mouth, backing up a gang of Spanish pickpockets on the streets of Paris, posing as policemen who arrest a gang member while the others rifle the pockets and purses of gawkers. When all of the gang except Richard and Philippe are pinched, things look grim. Plus, Richard insists that they take in a wide-eyed immigrant lad, a deaf-mute left behind in the arrests. Philippe suggests a three-person pickpocket trick, using the boy, but when that goes spectacularly badly, they hit rock bottom. Then, at the cinema, the lad finds a solution. It‘s time to celebrate.

Title: At Night
Plot: Christmas and New Year. Three girls between 18 and 20, are hospitalized with cancer. All three of them have serious problems, not just in terms of health, but also in terms of their relationships with their nearest and dearest. The girls find a haven in each other‘s company, where they are free from the fear of death and loneliness, and a substantial part of the film describes their sense of humor, unrestrained candidness and uncompromising zest for life.

Title: The Substitute
Plot: There is something strange about the new substitute teacher in class.

Title: Tanghi argentini
Plot: An office clerk with a hankering to tango enlists the support of a workplace colleague as he prepares for a date. It‘s Christmas time and the concept of giving assumes fairy tale proportions in this beguiling modern story.

Title: The Tonto Woman
Plot: A white woman is kidnapped from her home by Apache Indians. Traded to the Mojave Indians, she lives as a squaw for 11 years until she is found by her husband. Unfit for society he keeps her in a shack in the desert. Her solitary existence is transformed with the arrival of a Mexican. He befriends her, reignites her self-worth and increases her confidence. He re-introduces her to her husband and leaves. As he is leaving town he is ambushed by her husbands men and there is a gun-battle. Who lives and who dies?

Title: Freeheld
Plot: Lieutenant Laurel Hester is dying. All she wants to do is leave her pension benefits to her life partner - Stacie, so Stacie can afford to keep their house. Laurel is told no; they are not husband and wife. After spending a lifetime fighting for justice for other people, Laurel - a veteran New Jersey detective - launches a final battle for justice. Knuckle-biting, dramatic Freeheld chronicles a dying policewoman‘s bitter fight to provide for the love of her life.

Title: La corona
Plot: The contestants are murderers, guerrillas, and thieves. The winner will be crowned Queen, but she won‘t be invited on a press tour as a role model for young girls. Instead, she will be escorted back to her cell.

Title: Salim Baba
Plot: Salim Muhammad is a 55-year-old man who lives in North Kolkata with his wife and five children. Since the age of ten he has made a living using a hand-cranked projector to screen discarded film scraps for the kids in his surrounding neighborhoods.

Title: Sari‘s Mother
Plot: An Iraqi mother seeks health care for her 10-year-old son, who is dying of AIDS, against a background of war and occupation.

Title: Taxi to the Dark Side
Plot: An in-depth look at the torture practices of the United States in Afghanistan, Iraq and Guantanamo Bay, focusing on an innocent taxi driver in Afghanistan who was tortured and killed in 2002.

Title: No End in Sight
Plot: A comprehensive look at the Bush Administration‘s conduct of the Iraq war and its occupation of the country.

Title: Operation Homecoming: Writing the Wartime Experience
Plot: A unique documentary about troops‘ experiences in Iraq and Afghanistan, based on writings by soldiers, Marines, and air men. Some writings were published in the New Yorker in summer 2006. A larger assortment was published as a book by Random House last September. The film drew upon the submissions by soldiers for the book. It‘s a remarkable portrait of troops at war - the complexities, doubts, and fears - written with honesty. The 81-minute version of the film (which will be in theatres) includes 11 pieces of writing, with different visual strategies, along with interviews with the writers, and with more established American writers who are also veterans. In the latter group are Tim O‘Brien, Yusef Komunyakaa, Tobias Wolff, Joe Haldeman, James Salter, Anthony Swofford, Richard Currey, and Paul Fussell. The visual approaches range from poet Brian Turner reading directly to camera, to archival footage, to an animated graphic novel
ReleaseYear: to a still photo sequence shot by photographer Antonin Kratochvil. It‘s rooted in a program by the NEA that created a series of writing workshops at military bases. After those workshops, the writers submitted pieces for consideration in the book, edited by Andy Carroll. From those writings were selected 11 for inclusion in the film. There is also a 53-minute version of this film which will be airing on PBS as part of the series America at a Crossroads" in April
RunningTime: 2007. Both of these are different from the other film ‘Operation Homecoming" from 2007
GradeID: directed by Lawrence Bridges. That piece was produced by the NEA as a documentary about their writing workshops."

Title: Sicko
Plot: A documentary comparing the highly profitable American health care industry to other nations, and HMO horror stories.

Title: War Dance
Plot: Three children living in a displacement camp in northern Uganda compete in their country‘s national music and dance festival.

Title: Persepolis
Plot: Poignant coming-of-age story of a precocious and outspoken young Iranian girl that begins during the Islamic Revolution.

Title: Surf‘s Up
Plot: A behind-the-scenes look at the annual Penguin World Surfing Championship, and its newest participant, up-and-comer Cody Maverick.

Title: Mr Hublot
Plot: Mr Hublot is a withdrawn, idiosyncratic character with OCD, scared of change and the outside world. Robot Pet‘s arrival turns his life upside down: he has to share his home with this very invasive companion.

Title: Feral
Plot: A wild boy is found in the woods by a solitary hunter and brought back to civilization. Alienated by a strange new environment, the boy tries to adapt by using the same strategies that kept him safe in the forest.

Title: Get a Horse!
Plot: Mickey, Minnie, Horace Horsecollar, and Clarabelle Cow go on a musical wagon ride until Peg-Leg Pete tries to run them off the road.

Title: Possessions
Plot: One night of the eighteenth century, in the depths of the mountain, a human being is lost and finds a small temple. In the moment when he enters the room space is transformed into a completely different world.

Title: Room on the Broom
Plot: To the annoyance of her cat a kindly witch allows a dog, a bird and a frog who have helped her retrieve things she has lost to ride on her broomstick, making it top heavy. The broom is destroyed by a fire-breathing dragon who threatens to eat the witch but the creatures band together to impersonate a monster and save her. As a result she fashions a luxurious new broom with seats on which they can all ride comfortably.

Title: Helium
Plot: A young boy Alfred is dying, but through the stories about HELIUM - a magical fantasy world, told by the hospital‘s eccentric janitor Enzo, Alfred regain the joy and happiness of his life, and finds a safe haven away from daily life.

Title: Just Before Losing Everything
Plot: Miriam, with her two children, escapes her husband, whom she fears.

Title: Do I Have to Take Care of Everything?
Plot: A chaotic morning in a family with kids, and a mother who is determined that it‘s best to take care of everything herself.

Title: The Voorman Problem
Plot: Doctor Williams is the latest psychiatrist to deal with a smug patient called Voorman who claims to be God himself. Although skeptical, Williams soon gets an eerie feeling that openly malicious Voorman is not simply insane.

Title: The Lady in Number 6: Music Saved My Life
Plot: Alice Herz-Sommer, aged 109 and the world‘s oldest Holocaust survivor, tells the story of how music saved her life: both during her time at Theresienstadt concentration camp and in the years afterwards.

Title: Cavedigger
Plot: In this OSCAR® NOMINATED documentary short, artist Ra Paulette digs other-worldly, sculptural caves using nothing but hand tools. But, as patrons cut off his projects due to lack of funds or artistic differences, Paulette‘s frustration mounts. This penetrating portrait examines the cost of Paulette‘s obsession and tracks him as he rejects commissions for his own 10-year Magnum Opus.

Title: Facing Fear
Plot: The worlds of a former neo-Nazi and the gay victim of his senseless hate crime attack collide by chance 25 years after the incident that dramatically shaped both of their lives. They proceed to embark on a journey of forgiveness that challenges both to grapple with their beliefs and fears, eventually leading to an improbable collaboration...and friendship.

Title: Karama Has No Walls
Plot: ‘Karama has no walls‘ is set amidst Yemen‘s 2011 uprising. The film illustrates the nature of the Yemeni revolution in stark contrast to the gross violations of human rights that took place on Friday, March 18th 2011. Juma‘at El-Karama (Friday of Dignity) marks a turning point in the Yemeni revolution as the tragic events that took place on this day -when pro-government snipers shot dead 53 protestors - shook the nation and propelled hundreds of thousands more to flock to the square in solidarity with their fellow citizens. Through the lenses of two cameramen and the accounts of two fathers, the film retells the story of the people behind the statistics and news reports, encapsulating the tragic events of the day as they unfolded.

Title: Prison Terminal: The Last Days of Private Jack Hall
KoreanTitle: 프리즌 터미널: 잭 홀 일병의 마지막 나날
Plot: Prison Terminal: The Last Days of Private Jack Hall is a moving cinema verite documentary that breaks through the walls of one of Americas oldest maximum security prisons to tell the story of the final months in the life of a terminally ill prisoner and the hospice volunteers, they themselves prisoners, who care for him. The film draws from footage shot over a six-month period behind the walls of the Iowa State Penitentiary and provides a fascinating and often poignant account of how the hospice experience can profoundly touch even the forsaken lives of the incarcerated.

Title: 20 Feet from Stardom
Plot: Backup singers live in a world that lies just beyond the spotlight. Their voices bring harmony to the biggest bands in popular music, but we‘ve had no idea who these singers are or what lives they lead, until now.

Title: The Act of Killing
Plot: A documentary which challenges former Indonesian death-squad leaders to reenact their mass-killings in whichever cinematic genres they wish, including classic Hollywood crime scenarios and lavish musical numbers.

Title: Cutie and the Boxer
Plot: This candid New York love story explores the chaotic 40-year marriage of famed boxing painter Ushio Shinohara and his wife, Noriko. Anxious to shed her role as her overbearing husband‘s assistant, Noriko finds an identity of her own.

Title: Dirty Wars
Plot: Investigative journalist Jeremy Scahill is pulled into an unexpected journey as he chases down the hidden truth behind America‘s expanding covert wars.

Title: The Square
Plot: A group of Egyptian revolutionaries battle leaders and regimes, risking their lives to build a new society of conscience.

Title: The Great Beauty
Plot: Jep Gambardella has seduced his way through the lavish nightlife of Rome for decades, but after his 65th birthday and a shock from the past, Jep looks past the nightclubs and parties to find a timeless landscape of absurd, exquisite beauty.

Title: The Broken Circle Breakdown
Plot: Elise and Didier fall in love at first sight, in spite of their differences. He talks, she listens. He‘s a romantic atheist, she‘s a religious realist. When their daughter becomes seriously ill, their love is put on trial.

Title: The Hunt
Plot: A teacher lives a lonely life, all the while struggling over his son‘s custody. His life slowly gets better as he finds love and receives good news from his son, but his new luck is about to be brutally shattered by an innocent little lie.

Title: The Missing Picture
Plot: Rithy Panh uses clay figures, archival footage, and his narration to recreate the atrocities Cambodia‘s Khmer Rouge committed between 1975 and 1979.

Title: Omar
Plot: A young Palestinian freedom fighter agrees to work as an informant after he‘s tricked into an admission of guilt by association in the wake of an Israeli soldier‘s killing.

Title: The Croods
Plot: 살던 동굴이 파괴된 후, 원시인 가족은 한 별난 소년의 도움을 받아 생소하고 환상적인 세계를 여행하게 된다.

Title: Ernest & Celestine
Plot: The story of an unlikely friendship between a bear, Ernest, and a young mouse named Celestine.

Title: The Wind Rises
Plot: A look at the life of Jiro Horikoshi, the man who designed Japanese fighter planes during World War II.

Title: Ted
Plot: 어린 시절 빈 소원으로 존 배넷의 테디 베어 인형인 테드가 살아 움직이게 되었고, 그 이후로 존과 함께 자랐다. 존이 어른이 되어 여자친구인 로리를 만나게 되었을 때, 존과 테드사이에 미묘한 대립이 생기게 된다.

Title: Chasing Ice
Plot: Follow National Geographic photographer James Balog across the Arctic as he deploys time-lapse cameras designed for one purpose: to capture a multi-year record of the world‘s changing glaciers.

Title: Paperman
Plot: An urban office worker finds that paper airplanes are instrumental in meeting a girl in ways he never expected.

Title: Adam and Dog
Plot: 에덴동산에서, 아담.그리고 한마리 개.

Title: Fresh Guacamole
Plot: Transforming familiar objects into fresh guacamole.

Title: Head Over Heels
Plot: After many years of marriage, Walter and Madge have grown apart: he lives on the floor and she lives on the ceiling. When Walter tries to reignite their old romance, their equilibrium comes crashing down, and the couple that can‘t agree which way is up must find a way put their marriage back together.

Title: The Longest Daycare
Plot: Maggie Simpson spends the day in the Ayn Rand School for Tots.

Title: Curfew
Plot: At the lowest point of his life, Richie gets a call from his estranged sister, asking him to look after his nine-year old niece, Sophia, for a few hours.

Title: Asad
Plot: A coming of age fable of a Somali boy as he struggles to survive in his war-torn land.

Title: Buzkashi Boys
Plot: Set against the dramatic landscape of contemporary Afghanistan and the National sport of Buzkashi - a brutal game of horse polo played with a dead goat - Buzkashi Boys tells the coming of age story of two best friends, a charismatic street urchin and a defiant blacksmith‘s son, who struggle to realize their dreams as they make their way to manhood in one of the most war-torn countries on Earth. Shot on location in Kabul city by an alliance of Afghan and international film makers, Buzkashi Boys is a look at the life that continues beyond the headlines of war in Afghanistan.

Title: Death of a Shadow
Plot: Stuck in a dark limbo between life and death, a deceased soldier Nathan Rijckx collects shadows of dying men and women to buy back his own second chance at life. Obsessed by a girl he met the moment before he died, the thought of seeing his beloved again drives the soldier to regain access to the world of the living. But when he discovers that she‘s already in love with someone else, jealousy clouds his mind and pushes him toward a bitter decision, a decision not without its consequences...

Title: Henry
Plot: Henry, a great concert pianist, has his life thrown in turmoil the day the love of this life, Maria, disappears mysteriously. He‘ll then discover the inevitable verdict of life.

Title: Inocente
Plot: A personal and vibrant coming of age story about a young artist‘s determination never to surrender to the bleakness of her surroundings. At 15, Inocente refuses to let her dream of becoming an artist be caged by being an undocumented immigrant forced to live homeless for the last nine years. Color is her personal revolution and its sweep on her canvases creates a world that looks nothing like her own dark past. ‘Inocente‘ is both a timeless story about the transformative power of art and a timely snapshot of the new face of homelessness in America: children. The challenges are staggering, but the hope in her story proves that the hand she has been dealt does not define her, her dreams do.

Title: Kings Point
Plot: A documentary on five seniors living in a retirement resort in Florida - men and women who came decades ago with their spouses by their sides, and now find themselves grappling with love, loss and the universal desire for human connection.

Title: Mondays at Racine
Plot: Every third Monday of the month, two bold, brassy sisters open the doors of their Long Island hair salon to women diagnosed with cancer. As locks of hair fall to the floor, women gossip, giggle, weep, face their fears, and discover unexpected beauty.

Title: Open Heart
Plot: Eight Rwandan children leave their families behind to embark on a life-or-death journey seeking high-risk heart surgery in Sudan. Their hearts ravaged by a treatable disease from childhood strep throat, they have only months left to live. Open Heart reveals the intertwined endeavors of Dr. Emmanuel, Rwanda‘s lone government cardiologist fighting to save the lives of his young patients, and Dr. Gino, the Salam Center‘s head surgeon, who is fighting to save his hospital, Africa‘s only link to life-saving free cardiac surgery for the millions who need it.

Title: Redemption
Plot: Redemption is a documentary about New York City‘s canners - the men and women who survive by redeeming bottles and cans they collect from curbs, garbage cans and apartment complexes. You‘ve seen them combing through the trash, but never got to meet them. The film is an unexpected and intimate look at post-industrial gleaners, struggling at the edge of our society.

Title: Searching for Sugar Man
Plot: Two South Africans set out to discover what happened to their unlikely musical hero, the mysterious 1970s rock ‘n‘ roller, Rodriguez.

Title: Five Broken Cameras
Plot: A documentary on a Palestinian farmer‘s chronicle of his nonviolent resistance to the actions of the Israeli army.

Title: The Gatekeepers
Plot: A documentary featuring interviews with all surviving former heads of Shin Bet, the Israeli security agency whose activities and membership are closely held state secrets.

Title: How to Survive a Plague
Plot: The story of two coalitions -- ACT UP and TAG (Treatment Action Group) -- whose activism and innovation turned AIDS from a death sentence into a manageable condition.

Title: The Invisible War
Plot: An investigative documentary about the epidemic of rape of soldiers within the US military.

Title: War Witch
Plot: Somewhere in Sub-Saharan Africa, Komona, a 14-year-old girl, tells her unborn child growing inside her the story of her life since she has been at war. Everything started when she was abducted by the rebel army at the age of 12.

Title: No
Plot: An ad executive comes up with a campaign to defeat Augusto Pinochet in Chile‘s 1988 referendum.

Title: A Royal Affair
Plot: A young queen, who is married to an insane king, falls secretly in love with her physician - and together they start a revolution that changes a nation forever.

Title: Kon-Tiki
Plot: Legendary explorer Thor Heyerdal‘s epic 4,300-mile crossing of the Pacific on a balsawood raft in 1947, in an effort to prove that it was possible for South Americans to settle in Polynesia in pre-Columbian times.

Title: Brave
Plot: 괄괄한 성격의 스코틀랜드 공주가 세 귀족의 분노를 자극하고 소원을 잘못 빌어 세상이 엉망이 된다. 그녀는 이세 잘못을 수습해야 만 한다.

Title: Frankenweenie
Plot: Young Victor conducts a science experiment to bring his beloved dog Sparky back to life, only to face unintended, sometimes monstrous, consequences.

Title: ParaNorman
Plot: A misunderstood boy takes on ghosts, zombies and grown-ups to save his town from a centuries-old curse.

Title: The Pirates! Band of Misfits
Plot: Pirate Captain sets out on a mission to defeat his rivals Black Bellamy and Cutlass Liz for the Pirate of the year Award. The quest takes Captain and his crew from the shores of Blood Island to the foggy streets of Victorian London.

Title: Wreck-It Ralph
Plot: A video game villain wants to be a hero and sets out to fulfill his dream, but his quest brings havoc to the whole arcade where he lives.

Title: Avengers: Age of Ultron
Plot: 토니 스타크는 하이드라를 쫒던 중 치타우리 셉터를 탈환하고, 이를 이용하여 인류의 평화를 위한 인공지능을 만들려고 한다. 하지만 잘못된 일로 인해 인류를 말살하는 것이 목표인 울트론이 탄생하게 된다. 이를 막는 것은 어벤저스에 달려 있다.

Title: Captain America: The First Avenger
Plot: 2차 세계대전 당시, 군 입대 신체검사에서 번번히 탈락한 스티브 로저스는 수퍼 솔저 혈청을 맞고 캡틴 아메리카로 거듭나 나찌의 과학 부서인 하이드라와 싸우게 된다.

Title: Warm Bodies
Plot: 특이한 한 좀비가 한 소녀를 구한 후, 한 좀비와 한 소녀는 좀비가 창궐한 세상 전체를 변화시킬 수 있는 특별한 관계에 빠진다.

Title: The Deep Blue Sea
Plot: 영국에서 판사로 일하고 있는 윌리엄의 아내 헤스터는 답답한 결혼 생활을 이어가고 있다. 그러던 중 그녀는 왕실 비행기 조종사로 일하는 프레디를 만나 자기 파괴적인 사랑에 빠지게 된다. 깊어져 가는 소유욕은 집착을 낳고, 이 치명적 사랑은 결국 파멸로 치닿기 시작한다.

Title: Jurassic World
Plot: 쥬라기 공원(1993년)에서 20여년이 지난 후, 이슬라 누블라는설립자 존 해먼드의 유지를 받들어 쥬라기 월드라는 공룡 테마파크가 되어 개장했다. 10년동안 운영한 결과 방문자는 감소하고, 이를 만회하기 위해 방문자가 흥미있어 할만한 새로운 어트랙션이 만들어진다. 이는 무서운 일을 초래한다.

Title: Thor

Title: Thor: The Dark World

ReleaseYear: 존 코너는 저항군을 이끌며 스카이넷과 마지막 전쟁을 치른다."

Title: The Departed

Title: Babel

Plot: 미국과 일본의 세계 2차 대전중 이오지마에서 벌어진 전투이야기로, 일본인의 관점에서 본 이야기.

Title: Little Miss Sunshine

Plot: 다이아나 공주가 죽은 후, 엘리자베스 2세는 왜 그녀의 반응을 아무도 예측할 수 없었는지 고민한다.

Title: The Last King of Scotland
Plot: 잔인한 우간다의 독재자 이디 아민 정권의 실제 이야기로, 소설 <The Last King of Scotland>의 영화화

Title: Blood Diamond
Plot: 어부, 밀수업자, 다이어몬드 산업 신디케이트가 아프리카의 다이어몬드를 차지하기 위해 불법적인 일을 하게된다.

Title: Half Nelson
Plot: An inner-city junior high school teacher with a drug habit forms an unlikely friendship with one of his students after she discovers his secret.

Title: The Pursuit of Happyness
Plot: A struggling salesman takes custody of his son as he‘s poised to begin a life-changing professional endeavor.

Title: Venus
Plot: Life for a pair of veteran actors gets turned upside down after they meet a brash teenager.

Title: The Devil Wears Prada
Plot: 똑똑하지만 합리적인 사회 초년생 앤디는 까다롭기로 소문난 패션 잡지 편집장 미란다 프로스트의 비서 일을 시작한다.

Title: Little Children
Plot: The lives of two lovelorn spouses from separate marriages, a registered sex offender, and a disgraced ex-police officer intersect as they struggle to resist their vulnerabilities and temptations in suburban Connecticut.

Plot: A veteran high school teacher befriends a younger art teacher, who is having an affair with one of her 15-year-old students. However, her intentions with this new friend" also go well beyond platonic friendship."

Title: Dreamgirls

Plot: A real time account of the events on United Flight 93, one of the planes hijacked on 9/11 that crashed near Shanksville, Pennsylvania when passengers foiled the terrorist plot.

Title: Pan‘s Labyrinth
KoreanTitle: 판의 미로 - 오필리아와 세 개의 열쇠
Plot: 1944년 팔랑헤 정권하의 스페인에서, 가학적인 군인의 수양딸인 책을 좋아하는 소녀는 기괴한 곳으로 탈출하지만 판타지 세계에 사로잡한다.

Title: Borat: Cultural Learnings of America for Make Benefit Glorious Nation of Kazakhstan
KoreanTitle: 보랏 : 카자흐스탄 킹카의 미국문화 빨아 들이기
Plot: Kazakh TV talking head Borat is dispatched to the United States to report on the greatest country in the world. With a documentary crew in tow, Borat becomes more interested in locating and marrying Pamela Anderson.

Title: Children of Men
Plot: In 2027, in a chaotic world in which women have become somehow infertile, a former activist agrees to help transport a miraculously pregnant woman to a sanctuary at sea.

Title: The Black Dahlia
Plot: Two policemen see their personal and professional lives fall apart in the wake of the Black Dahlia" murder investigation."

Title: The Illusionist
Plot: In turn-of-the-century Vienna, a magician uses his abilities to secure the love of a woman far above his social standing.

Title: The Prestige
Plot: Two stage magicians engage in competitive one-upmanship in an attempt to create the ultimate stage illusion.

Title: The Good Shepherd
Plot: The tumultuous early history of the Central Intelligence Agency is viewed through the prism of one man‘s life.

Title: Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Man‘s Chest
Plot: 잭 스패로우는 지옥 살이를 피하려고 데비 존스에게 영혼으로 빛을 갚는다.

Title: Marie Antoinette
Plot: The retelling of France‘s iconic but ill-fated queen, Marie Antoinette. From her betrothal and marriage to Louis XVI at 15 to her reign as queen at 19 and to the end of her reign as queen and ultimately the fall of Versailles.

Title: 滿城盡帶黃金甲 (Curse of the Golden Flower)
Plot: During China‘s Tang dynasty the emperor has taken the princess of a neighboring province as wife. She has borne him two sons and raised his eldest. Now his control over his dominion is complete, including the royal family itself.

Title: Apocalypto
Plot: As the Mayan kingdom faces its decline, the rulers insist the key to prosperity is to build more temples and offer human sacrifices. Jaguar Paw, a young

Title: Flags of Our Fathers
Plot: The life stories of the six men who raised the flag at The Battle of Iwo Jima, a turning point in WWII.

Title: Poseidon
Plot: On New Year‘s Eve, the luxury ocean liner, Poseidon, capsizes after being swamped by a rogue wave. The survivors are left to fight for survival as they attempt to escape the sinking ship.

Title: Superman Returns
Plot: 수퍼맨은 크립톤의 잔해를 찾아 지구를 떠난후 5년만에 귀환한다. 5년 후, 연인 로이스 레인은 다른 남자와 결혼했고, 그의 오랜 적은 크립톤 행성의 기술로 세계를 위협에 빠트린다.

Title: Click
Plot: A workaholic architect finds a universal remote that allows him to fast-forward and rewind to different parts of his life. Complications arise when the remote starts to overrule his choices.

Title: An Inconvenient Truth
Plot: A documentary on Al Gore‘s campaign to make the issue of global warming a recognized problem worldwide.

Title: Cars
Plot: A hot-shot race-car named Lightning McQueen gets waylaid in Radiator Springs, where he finds the true meaning of friendship and family.

Title: The Good German
Plot: While in post-war Berlin to cover the Potsdam Conference, an American military journalist is drawn into a murder investigation which involves his former mistress and his driver.

Title: The Danish Poet
Plot: A woman ponders over the strange coincidences that made her forefathers and -mothers meet and create the premises for her becoming the person that she is.

Title: Lifted
Plot: A teenage alien tries to abduct a sleeping human, but with so many switches to do so, it‘s nearly impossible.

Title: The Little Matchgirl
Plot: An animated short based on Hans Christian Andersen‘s tale about a poor young girl with a burning desire to find comfort and happiness in her life. Desperate to keep warm, the girl lights the matches she sells, and envisions a very different life for herself in the fiery flames filled with images of loving relatives, bountiful food, and a place to call home.

Title: Maestro
Plot: Five minutes before his big performance, the Maestro and his persistent mechanical assistant are getting ready. As the clock ticks, life at the top is not all it seems.

Title: No Time for Nuts

David, an Israeli soldier, falls in love with Fatima, a beautiful Palestinian cashier, despite the animosity between their families‘ dueling restaurants. Can the couple‘s love withstand a 58-year-old conflict and their families‘ desire to control the future of the chick pea in the Middle East?

Title: Binta and the Great Idea
Plot: Binta, a little girl from Senegal, tells us about the everyday life in her village, the importance of education for the girls, and about her father‘s great idea to make the world a better place.

Plot: After an elderly man locks himself in a closet at a nursing home, his son and daughter try to persuade him to come out.

Title: The Saviour
Plot: A young Church elder struggles with his faith when the married woman he has been seeing breaks off their relationship.

Title: One Too Many
Plot: After his wife leaves him, Joaquin brings his mother-in-law back home to look after him and his son.

Title: Recycled Life

Title: Rehearsing a Dream

Every year a group of the country‘s most gifted 17-year-old performing and visual artists - singled out among thousands of their peers - share a week of dreams as they learn from mentors like Mikhail Baryshnikov, Vanessa Williams, Jacques d‘Amboise, Michael Tilson Thomas... and from each other. For seven transformative days, the passionate young artists revel in the support, encouragement and attention they have earned.

Title: Two Hands: The Leon Fleisher Story
Plot: 1964 년 레온 플라이셔 (Leon Fleisher)는 최고의 콘서트 피아니스트로 였습니다. 하지만, 사소한 사고로 오른손 엄지손가락을 잘라아야 하는 디스토니아가 발생했습니다. 최근 인터뷰에서 플라이셔는 결혼, 절망과 실망을 반복한 끝에 1983 년 수술후 콘서트 홀로 잠시 돌아 왔으며 마지막으로 Botox와 Rolfing과 함께 두 손으로 연주하는 능력에 대해 이야기했습니다.

Plot: 오스카상 수상자 Laura Poitras의 이라크 전쟁에 관한 다큐멘터리.

Plot: Stories from modern day Iraq as told by Iraqis living in a time of war, occupation and ethnic tension.

It focuses on a relationship between one of the widows, who wants to escape the social restrictions imposed on widows, and a man who is from the highest caste and a follower of Mahatma Gandhi.

Plot: Into the world of the Emperor Penguins, who find their soul mates through song, a penguin is born who cannot sing. But he can tap dance something fierce!

Title: Monster House

Title: Crash
Plot: Los Angeles citizens with vastly separate lives collide in interweaving stories of race, loss and redemption.

Title: Brokeback Mountain
Plot: 두 카우보이의 숨겨진, 비밀스러운 관계와 그 후의 삶에 얽힌 이야기

Title: Capote
Plot: 1959년, 트루먼 카포티는 캔사스 가족 살인에 대해 알게되고 이 사건에 대한 책을 쓰기로 결심한다. 소설을 위해 냉혹한 조사를 하는 동안, 카포티는 살인자 중의 한명인 사형수 페리 스미스와 어떤 관계를 만들게 된다.

Title: Good Night, and Good Luck.
Plot: 방송 저널리스트인 에드워드 R. 머로우는 하원의원 조셉 매카시를 살펴보게 된다.

Title: Munich
Plot: Based on the true story of the Black September aftermath, about the five men chosen to eliminate the ones responsible for that fateful day.

Plot: Nitta Sayuri reveals how she transcended her fishing-village roots and became one of Japan‘s most celebrated geisha.

Title: The New World

Title: Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire
Plot: Harry finds himself mysteriously selected as an under-aged competitor in a dangerous tournament between three schools of magic.

Title: Charlie and the Chocolate Factory
Plot: A young boy wins a tour through the most magnificent chocolate factory in the world, led by the world‘s most unusual candy maker.

Title: The Chronicles of Narnia: The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe
KoreanTitle: 나니아 연대기: 사자, 마녀, 그리고 옷장
Plot: 네 명의 아이들이 옷장을 통해 나니아의 땅으로 여행을 떠나고 신비로운 사자로 인해  그 아이들이 나니아를 해방할 운명을 타고 나니아로 오게 된 것을 알게 된다.

Title: War of the Worlds
Plot: As Earth is invaded by alien tripod fighting machines, one family fights for survival.

Plot: 클론 전쟁이 끝난 후, 파드메의 미래에 대한 환상을 보게 된 아나킨 스카이워커는 공화정과 사랑하는 여자, 그리고 제다이 사이에서 갈등을 일으킨다. 결국 포스의 어두운 면에 사로잡혀 다스 베이더로 각성하게 되고, 스승 오비완과 마지막 결전을 벌이게 된다.

Title: The Moon and the Son: An Imagined Conversation
Plot: The Moon and the Son, a 30-minute autobiographical animated film by John Canemaker, explores the difficult emotional terrain of father/son relationships as seen through Canemaker‘s own turbulent relationship with his father. Featuring the voices of noted actors Eli Wallach and John Turturro in the roles of father and son, The Moon and the Son combines memory, fact, conjecture, trial transcripts, audio recordings, home movies, photos, snapshots, and original animation to tell the story of an Italian immigrant‘s troubled life and the devastating consequences of his actions on his family.
A rag doll fights a monster that has been stealing the souls of his people.

Title: Badgered
Plot: Two crows disturb a badger‘s hibernation. The badger climbs out of its hole once to try to silence the crows. When that doesn‘t work, fate intervenes and the hill on which are the crow‘s tree and the badger‘s lair becomes an underground missile silo. The badger investigates, and events move beyond its control. Is sleep in the offing?

Title: The Mysterious Geographic Explorations of Jasper Morello
Plot: Set in a world of iron dirigibles and steam powered computers, this gothic horror mystery tells the story of Jasper Morello, a disgraced aerial navigator who flees his plague-ridden home on a desperate voyage to redeem himself.

Title: One Man Band

Title: Six Shooter
Plot: A black and bloody Irish comedy about a sad train journey where an older man, whose wife has died that morning, encounters a strange and possibly psychotic young oddball....

Title: The Runaway
Plot: On a winter day, Walter Dahlman is getting ready for a job interview; he‘s an unemployed architect in Hamburg. As he leaves his flat with little time to spare, a boy of about eight stops him in the hall and asks for a ride to school. Walter doesn‘t know the lad, who says he‘s Yuri. The boy is persistent; Walter, who has only a bicycle, ends up giving Yuri a lift to school. The boy calls him Daddy
ReleaseYear: and it‘s just the beginning of Walter‘s trials and tribulations. Who is the boy, where is his mother, and why Walter?

Title: The Last Farm
Plot: In a remote and windswept valley somewhere in the rugged landscapes of Iceland, a solitary elderly couple prepares for the forthcoming winter; however, the urge to work in such a feverish haste remains unknown.

Title: A Note of Triumph: The Golden Age of Norman Corwin

Title: March of the Penguins

Title: Everything in This Country Must
Plot: Northern Ireland. Soldiers, through inattention, run into a car with a woman and her young son. Two years later, a horse is stuck in the river, and the soldiers happen along, but the

Title: Little Terrorist

Title: Two Cars, One Night

Plot: 1963년 5월 2일, 아이들은 버밍험 알라배마의 분리를 막기위해 거리로 나섰다.

And he finds love.
